Anna Moyer of WDNR present--beautiful warm day with almost no breeze--aquatic plant growth in Fawn Lake is incredibly advanced compared to the other 8 lakes I've been on in last 10 days--EWM definitely ready to treat and is heaviest towards dam--as we went east- there were fewer big patches of EWM- but more patches of CLP--map sent to chemical applicator- Scott Provost- + Fawn District Board--milfoil sample taken for DNA testing--these plants are definitely ready to treat NOW--instructions + supplies for residue testing were given to Dave Sura last Saturday- so if treatment occurs soon- Lake District should be ready to do testing--also took sample of Lymnothamnus barbatus (I think)- pulling up a big patch
